result.name: Happy Veggies

reviews.text:
Amazing vegan food and a real gem of a place. 

All the wait staff are deaf, but they were really attentive, friendly and helpful. I love that this restaurant is run as a charity and really hope they are able to continue to do good work. 

The food is so good and they try to use as little salt as possible. I could not recommend it more highly.

This is one of our favourite eateries in HK -- a vegetarian paradise. This place employs the hard of hearing, and these workers are diligent, helpful and friendly. Food is cooked without MSG and without excessive oil, which is rare for Asian vegetarian eateries. Even carnivores should find certain dishes like sweet and sour fried mushrooms appealing. The place is especially popular during working day lunch times as the three choices set lunch is good value. For those who don't speak Chinese or know sign language, the menu is in English and Chinese, with pictures.
Great food and service. Huge portion sizes. Very friendly. Got a free soup to start and all in all we had a lovely time. Highly recommend!!

Very clean, healthy and delicious vegetarian fare. I had a bowl of mushroom dumpling soup, and small sides of pickled cucumber and guava salad. They’ve got a great mission to help us eat healthier while giving back to the community by hiring hearing impaired servers. On the weekend there are no set menus and you have to order a la cart and so it’s a bit more expensive for that way and they do add 10% service charge but that comes with a cute teapot.

Cantonese vegetarian restaurant with lots and lots of choices. We ordered three cold sides and the fried bean curd with mushroom filling for 198HKD all up. Pricing is reasonable and food is tasty. This place employs death people so please be patient when placing orders. Menus in English are quite straightforward to navigate.
